#Edit the file like this:
#
#Type sudo nano /private/etc/hosts to command line (and enter password)
#Now, you can add as many entries as needed using the text editor. To navigate the
#text editor, use the arrow keys to move between lines and hit enter to create a new line.
#
#Just as with other operating systems, use the following format:
#
#1.2.3.4 yoursite.com
#
#Enter each IP address on its own line. For each IP address, you can add multiple hostnames
#on the same line.
#
#To save your changes, type Control + X.
